column12: Isolated DNA encoding the Not I restriction endonuclease and related methods for producing the same.
column13: The present invention is directed to a method for cloning and producing the  Not I restriction endonuclease by 1) introducing the restriction endonuclease gene from  Nocardia otitidis-caviarum  into a host whereby the restriction gene is expressed; 2) fermenting the host which contains the plasmid encoding and expressing the  Not I restriction endonuclease activity, and 3) purifying the  Not I restriction endonuclease from the fermented host which contains the plasmid encoding and expressing the  Not I restriction endonuclease activity.

column12: CARBOHYDRATE OXIDASE AND USE THEREOF IN BAKING
column13: The properties of dough or bread can be improved by the addition of a carbohydrate oxidase which can oxidise the reducing end of an oligosaccharide more efficiently than the corresponding monosaccharide, e.g., preferentially oxidizing maltodextrins or cellodextrins over glucose. A novel carbohydrate oxidase having the capability to oxidize maltodextrins and cellodextrins more efficiently than glucose may be obtained from a strain of Microdochium, particulary M. nivale. The amino acid sequence of the novel carbohydrate oxidase has very low homology (<20 % identity) with known amino acid sequences.

column12: Breast tomosynthesis with flexible compression paddle
column13: A method of breast image reconstruction includes positioning a breast on an imaging system support plate, compressing the breast with a flexible paddle, obtaining imaging data, estimating a breast thickness profile by at least one of placing markers on the breast, performing an image-based analysis of the obtained data, using an auxiliary system, and performing a model-based computation. The three dimensional reconstruction including using a thickness profile of the breast surface in at least one of an iterative reconstruction, a filtered back-projection reconstruction, and a joint reconstruction performed using information obtained from an ultrasound scan. A non-transitory medium having executable instructions to cause a processor to perform the method is also disclosed.
column15: WANG XIN;;CLAUS BERNHARD ERICH HERMANN;;DAVIS CYNTHIA ELIZABETH LANDBERG;;IORDACHE RAZVAN GABRIEL

column13: A method of breast image reconstruction includes positioning a breast on an imaging system support plate, compressing the breast with a flexible paddle, obtaining imaging data, estimating a breast thickness profile by at least one of placing markers on the breast, performing an image-based analysis of the obtained data, using an auxiliary system, and performing a model-based computation. The three dimensional reconstruction including using a thickness profile of the breast surface in at least one of an iterative reconstruction, a filtered back-projection reconstruction, and a joint reconstruction performed using information obtained from an ultrasound scan. A non-transitory medium having executable instructions to cause a processor to perform the method is also disclosed.

column12: System and method for anatomy based reconstruction
column13: A technique is provided for performing diagnosis and/or analysis of a volumetric image generated via anatomy based reconstruction. The technique includes generating a three-dimensional image by reconstructing a plurality of residual projection images from which a contribution of one or more structures of interest has been removed. The technique also includes evaluating the three-dimensional image and/or the plurality of residual projection images to generate a diagnosis.

column12: Method for illustration of breast, involves positioning of breast in breast support, which has flexible diaphragm, and producing partial vacuum within flexible diaphragm
column13: The method involves positioning of breast in a breast support (12), which has a flexible diaphragm, and producing partial vacuum within the flexible diaphragm. The breast is illustrated by a medical picture giving technology. A vacuum pump (14) is provided for production of a partial vacuum, which is connected with the breast support. Independent claims are also included for the following: (1) a method for armament of a mammography system (2) a breast support, which has an outer casing and a base plate.

column12: MAMMA IMMOBILIZATION APPARATUS AND MAMMOGRAPHY
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a mammographic system and a mammography being comfortable for patients, maximizing the radiographing range of the mamma tissue in an examination, and facilitating the immobilization of the mamma during the examination.

SOLUTION: This mammography includes a step for positioning the mamma in a mamma retainer 12 including a flexible film 46, and a step for at least partially evacuating inside the flexible film. A method for improving the performance of the mammographic system and the mamma retainer having various constitutions are also provided. In another phase, the mammographic system is provided. This mammographic system includes an imaging beam generation source for supplying the imaging beam, and the mamma retainer for adapting itself to the mamma and immobilizing the mamma. The mamma retainer is connected to a vacuum pump for evacuating a part between the mamma and the mamma retainer. This system also includes a detector for detecting the imaging beam passing through the mamma, and a positioning unit for positioning the imaging beam generating source and the detection unit. The positioning unit aligns the imaging beam generation source, the mamma retainer and the detector on a same axis.

column12: Full field digital tomosynthesis method and apparatus
column13: A tomosynthesis system (1) for forming a three dimensional image of an object (2) is provided. The system includes an X-ray source (11) adapted to irradiate the object (2) with a beam (3) of X-rays from a plurality of positions in a sector, an X-ray detector (13) positioned relative to the X-ray source to detect X-rays transmitted through the object and a processor (21) which is adapted to generate a three dimensional image of the object based on X-rays detected by the detector. The detector is adapted to move (7) relative to the object and/or the X-ray source is adapted to irradiate the object with the beam of X-rays such that the beam of X-rays follows in a non arc shaped path and/or a center of the beam of X-rays impinges substantially on the same location on the detector from different X-ray source positions in the sector.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR ALL VISUAL FIELD DIGITAL TYPE TOMOSYNTHESIS
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a tomosynthesis system (1) for forming a three-dimensional image of a subject (2).

SOLUTION: The system comprises X-ray sources (11) which are fitted to irradiate the subject (2) by X-rays from plural positions in a sector, an X-ray detector (13) which detects X-rays passing through the subject, and a treatment device (21) which is fitted to create a three-dimensional image of the subject based on the detected X-rays. Then, in this system, the X-rays follow a non-circular arc pathway, or the center of the X-rays actually makes to hit the same position on the detector from different X-ray source positions in the sector and so the system is fitted to move the detector based on the subject, or the X-ray sources are fitted to irradiate the subject by the X-rays.
